<h2>Raiding Rules and Procedures</h2>

<p>Divine Prophecy has various guides and procedures for different raids that can be completed.&nbsp; We strongly encourage all members to visit the <a href="http://www.divineprophecy.org/Forum/forum_topics.asp?FID=12">FAQ Message Board</a>
and review these guides.</p>

<p>To ensure efficient raiding, this page is designed to provide the core basics to all guild-sponsored raids.</p>

<h4>Have Your Own Means of Egress</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>We usually do not have a
wizard.&nbsp; We seldom have enough druids.&nbsp; Adding to that, there are
unexpected thing like server crashes, power outages, ISP outages, prolonged
LD.&nbsp; You get the point.&nbsp; Gate potions are cheap and easy.<b>&nbsp; <i>It
is better to have a gate potion and never use it then to be stuck somewhere
with no way out.</i></b></p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Be On Time</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>For scheduled raids, make your own arrangements for transportation to the raid site.&nbsp; If
time is tight, do it the day before the raid.&nbsp; Its ok to ask in guild
chats for a port, but do not get upset if no one can come get you.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Reduce Spam</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>Please spam as little as possible.&nbsp; Ask for buffs with tells. &nbsp;Talk to friends in
tells.&nbsp; Do not send tells to the puller or RL asking them to pull
&quot;your&quot; mob.&nbsp; Stay off /OOC and shout.&nbsp; If you wish to, you
can set up your own spam channel.</p>
</blockquote>

<h4>Group Leaders Are To Keep Track Of Their Group</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>Let
someone know if you have a LD or AFK person.&nbsp; As group leader, this is
your job.&nbsp; In addition, let the person handling the grouping know if
someone left the raid.&nbsp; <i>DO NOT</i> start picking up people on your own.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Pay Attention</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>Missing something sometimes means all the difference between a narrow escape and a wipe.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Be Respectful Of Grouping</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>Do not whine about your group.&nbsp; It is ok to ask if the group maker realized you
do not have a healer.&nbsp; It is not ok to go on constantly because you do not
have a cleric.&nbsp; Hate raids have been run without a cleric in the past.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Death Happens</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>Do not come if you cannot afford to die.&nbsp; We all die at raids.&nbsp; We have
never lost a corpse yet.&nbsp; We have not missed a Rez since our first epic
attempt.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Stand Still</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>If you are not absolutely sure where you are going, then stand still.&nbsp; It’s a lot
easier to find you if your where we were, versus where ever you happened to run
off to.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Control the Buffing</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>Never heal or buff a FD puller unless he knows you are doing it, and okays it.&nbsp;
Otherwise, you will pick up his aggro and if he FD's the camp will be trained
or you will be summoned.&nbsp; Alternatively, DT'ed in the case of Fear.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Loot Categories</h4>
<blockquote>
<p><b>Raid Loot</b> – Loot that is not reserved or will be used for guild
funds.  This roll is invoked when all Tier
levels have passed on rolling for an item.</p>

<p><b>Greed Roll</b>– Loot that everyone can roll on.  You are free to use the loot as you wish.</p>

<p><b>Can and Will Use (Tier)</b> – This loot is considered 2-week
loot wins.  It should be rolled on if a
member feels it is an upgrade for them.  See <a href="loot.asp">Loot Rules</a> for more details.</p>

<p><b>Camped and Reserved Loot</b> - In some cases, loot may be
reserved.&nbsp; Including but not limited to this are epic drops, camped rare
spawns and upper extreme items like Breast Plates.&nbsp; In the case of camped
spawns, normally only the &quot;key&quot; item will be reserved.</p>

<p><b>Cash Loot</b> - This goes to the guild to cover cost involved in raiding.</p>
</blockquote>
<h4>Have Fun</h4>
<blockquote>
<p>You can be organized and have fun.&nbsp; If fact a well run raid is tons more fun than chaos.&nbsp; The loots much better too.</p>
</blockquote>
